sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I723016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Contains the DntR gene (encodes a transcriptional regulator activated by [salicylate]) under the control of its native promoter. To complete the system, clone the gene you want to induce under the control of promoter pDntA [insert BB # here later].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Scott Ramsay
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cloned from a historical plasmid based on pQF52 carrying genomic sequences from ''Burkholderia cepacia''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: '''''The precise boundaries of the promoters and ribosome binding sites are unknown, however they are known to exist back-to-back and were consequently cloned as one entire physical unit.'''''

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I723011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the naturally-occurring (possibly stationary-phase only) promoter for the DntR gene (which encodes the transcriptional regulator DntR) back-to-back with the DntR-regulated promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Scott Ramsay
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cloned from a historical plasmid based on pQF52 carrying genomic sequences from ''Burkholderia cepacia''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This does not physically exist as a basic part due to time constraints; it was cloned as part of composite part which incorporates all of the components necessary for expression of a reporter gene under the control of DntR. For this reason, the ends of the supplied sequence may not accurately represent the boundaries of the functional unit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: DntR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The protein encoded by DntR recognises environmental [salicylate] and undergoes a conformational change allowing it to, and positively regulate, the promoter for the gene DntA. DntR, therefore, should be used in combination with pDntA to acheive a switch that responds to [salicylate].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Scott Ramsay
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This transcriptional regulator is encoded in the opposite direction to that of its target promoter.
